An Osun State Magistrates’ court sitting in Osogbo on Thursday, ordered for the remand of Adijat Lukumon (52) for alleged stealing of jewelry. Though Adijat Lukumon admitted guilty to the two count charges levelled against her, the presiding magistrate, Mrs Risikat Olayemi ordered that the defendant be remanded in police custody to establish fact against her. The police prosecutor, Olayiwola Rasaq told the court that the defendant committed the offence on January 13, 2020 at Ilesa Garage area in Osogbo, Osun State capital. Rasaq stated further that the defendant allegedly stole some earrings worth N40,000 property of one Titilayo Adekunle. The offence according to him was committed contrary and punishable under section 390 and 249 cap 34 vol ll law of Osun State 2002. However, the defence counsel, Ibrahim. A. Imran prayed the court to temper justice with mercy on her client. The presiding Magistrate, Mrs Risikat Olayemi subsequently ordered that the defendant be remanded in police custody to establish fact against her as she adjourned the case to January 30, 2020.  